# Keep push-notifications doc in sync

[docs/push-notifications.md](../../docs/push-notifications.md) is the canonical
list of every remote push the app sends. If you add, remove, or change a push
notification — including its trigger, recipient set, title, body, or tap-target
URL — you MUST update that file in the same change.

Look for these patterns when deciding whether the doc needs an update:

- Calls to `send_push_to_group(...)` or `send_push_to_users(...)` in SQL
- New triggers on tables that fan out via `trigger_push_on_*` functions
- New `group_events` summaries (covered by the catch-all entry, but worth
  listing distinctively if user-facing wording differs)
- Client-side `db.rpc('send_push_to_users', ...)` calls in `js/`
- Changes to the APNs / Web Push edge functions that affect payload shape

For each push, the doc records: trigger, recipient, title, body, tap-target URL,
and the defining file + line range. Match the existing table format when adding
a new entry.
